This season we had a few what my teema calls “Power cycle problems”. Theas problems will just appear when you turn on the robot and will just go when restart.

Example 1:
Turning on the robot and our canivore and every device on the chain will indicate fault in can bus. WITHOUT touching anything but the main beaker, when turning off and on the robot the fault will be cleared and everything will work and indicate normal.

Example 2:
Sometimes when turning on the robot and connecting to it with a ethernet cable. Roborio robot code wont come up, when restarting the roborio the code will come up just as normal.

Thees problems are coming up in seemingly random times. Some days they are more rare then others.

I feel like thees season we had quite a few of them that are manly about can bus.

Do your team also encounter those problems? If so how do you deal with them? And what are you recommending us to check?

(All electrical components are up to date and used as intended by the manufacturer)

With the CANivore issue, are you powering the CANivore with just USB or are you also adding 12V from the PDP/H or VRM? Last year my team only powered the CANivore with the 5V (USB) and voltage drops would casue it to brown out and adding 12V power fixed our issues.
